social_posts.post_text: My cowboy gal.
I might be biased, but man I have some of the cutest kids ever.

Townes new saying as of lately- “I was born a gun shootin, winter man!” 

He also tells me how much he loves me at least 130 times a day, every night before bed he comes and hugs my belly & says “How ya doing in there little buddy?” & then proceeds to kiss my belly & run off to bed. I’m so happy he hopped in this photo the other day, it’s for sure become one of my forever favorites, especially with his little grin, & messy hair, I never want to forget this time in my little cowboys life & how much he loves & how he shows his love.

Happy birthday to my person, Zack you are the greatest person I know & I feel so lucky it’s you I get to share my life with. It’s been so fun looking back on pictures today of all the adventures we’ve gone on, the places we’ve traveled, our little family growing & growing & growing 😂, the good times, and even the bad times, these are all moments of life we’ve gotten to grow together & learn more about each other, this life God gave us, & these kids we get to raise together. All I know is there’s no one else I would rather share all these adventures with, I can’t wait to see what 34 holds for you old man. I love you so much, for all my days.

Sending you all love. I failed at Christmas cards this year, so here’s our virtual one. Thanks for sharing our journey with us & always showing us kindness & love. We wish you all a very merry Christmas & a happy & HEALTHY new year. 🎄
Sunsets & my family. My two favorite views.

Had a few people check on me pregnancy wise lately sooooo here we go, I’m 30 weeks & running out of things to wear…. I can not believe this surprise baby will be here so soon…feels like I just found out about you. Still no idea on gender, I was sure it was a girl at first, lately I’ve been thinking boy, and now I’m just not sure at all. We have no names, none, but also don’t send suggestions because names are one of those things that just feel right when you know, or at least for me they are, my other 3 kids names came at the perfect time & I know this baby’s name will too. Anyway, just a random update to let people know I’m still pregnant & not due until March 😊.

Y’all better have your alarm clocks set for tomorrow. I’m telling you now. This @tealcokeblake X @buckaroobabyco  collab is a cowkid mamas dream. My boys literally talk about hunting jackalopes on a weekly basis & @j_isforjackalope is one of our favorite books & now it’s on their Jammie’s & a blanket & a dress for luck 🥹, I just about die. Not to mention this rad Hereford heart print on jackets & jammies & blankets. @buckaroobabyco sent stuff for the baby too & i can not wait to wrap them up in all of this goodness. I literally could never say enough good things about buckaroo baby co & the quality & originality of their products. And obviously Teal is one of our favorite artists so when I tell you this is a collab of our dreams, we literally mean it, we can’t wait for the second edition of J is for Jackalope.

social_posts.post_text: Big Bertha & McGinnster. It was a memorable night for sure. Can’t wait for round 2 tonight. Thanks so much to @colterwall and his crew for having @zackmcginn and our crew out and treating us like family, we’re so very grateful.

I know these ice storms bring so much work & danger with them, but they seem to be creating some of my favorite memories with my family. Every year when these storms roll in the kiddos stay home from school & get to help chop ice & put out feed & some days they hate it, and other days like today they love it. It’s fun watching them learn & tell us about how they can’t wait to do it by themselves (as we hint to them that one day they will be doing it on their own & cursing us 😂). It takes a whole lot longer getting out of the house with all the layers & snacks packed, but I know I’ll never regret these days.

social_posts.post_text: Our time with just Luck at home is fleeting fast, it’s such an emotional roller coaster of looking forward to what’s coming & seeing her with her sibling, to feeling sad that our baby will no longer be the baby. She’s seriously the best little girl, she loves being a little cowgirl & wants to be involved in all ways, she loves her brothers & chasing them & playing with them, she’s so smart, & she’s just incredible in all ways. I just love her so much.

Happy Valentine’s Day to my guy. I’m realizing now that we don’t have many photos of just you & I in the last handful of years, there’s a kid or 3 some where in the mix, or a friend or 7. We’re pretty lucky to be so loved by so many kids & friends I guess 😂. As the years have gone by I still say silly things, make up my own silly songs, shake my big ol belly at you (maybe one day I won’t be big & pregnant during our marriage 😂).....& you look at me like I'm crazy every single time & after all these years I still get a kick out of it. But the thing is, you let me be me & you love me fiercely for it. And in return I love you fiercely for all that makes you, you. Thanks for the endless love. For all my days McGinn. I love you.

It’s impossible to not spill something on my belly at this point. Maybe, just might try to get some maternity photos tonight if I can find the energy to walk 😂. Also, final guesses people. 

Boy or girl? 
Birthdate?
Weight & length?

Any day now sweet baby, we’re ready for you. 

Any true & tried tips for natural induction, send them my way 🥲.
It’s go time 😊.

Vallie Joi McGinn 
March 6, 2023
5:10 pm 
7lbs 15oz 
19” long 

Welcome to the world my sweet, beautiful dark haired girl. You are SO LOVED. 

Every thing about you has been a surprise, from us getting pregnant with you naturally after years of fertility treatments for your siblings, to your rough pregnancy, and then incredibly fast & beautiful labor & delivery. You’ve only been here three days and you’ve already taught me you are going to be quite a little force to be reckoned with on this earth. I never knew I needed you, but God did, and I’m so glad his plan is so much bigger & better then mine. I love you so much Vallie Joi, thanks for choosing me to be your mom.

HAPPY BIRTHDAY to my sweet 6 year olds!!! 🥹. Did I absolutely cry looking at these photos I took this morning, 💯%. Time has gone absolutely too fast with these two. I’m so incredibly proud to be their mom. They are literally the coolest people I know, & they are 100% true to themselves. Townes is a cowboy through & through and has grown so much in the last year, he’s so sweet & thoughtful & really takes on the responsibility of ‘older’ brother & is always on the lookout for his siblings, he loves shooting guns, and dressing himself in pocket shirts everyday, he likes looking ‘fancy’ & dancing for the ladies he says. Kase is all about sports & dinos, he could probably name every Dino that’s ever lived by just looking at it, if he’s not learning about Dino’s he’s probably shooting a basketball or playing catch, kicking a soccer ball or doing some sport, he’s naturally talented & if he doesn’t get it at first he will try & try & try until he figures it out, Babe Ruth, Michael Jordan & Jackie Robinson are still his heroes. And the thing these two share in common is rock & roll, and their band ‘The Bandits’ they like rocking out, writing new songs, and yelling at me about how I need to drive them to Billy Bobs for their concert they think they’re going to put on….I have no doubt if they want to, one day they’ll make that happen. Keep your determination & uniqueness & I know y’all will go so many places in this life. I love you boys so much and I’m so happy you’re mine.

Sisters. 🌜🌛

So crazy to think…my sister & my brother are my absolute best friends in life, but growing up I always felt bad that my little brother didn’t have a ‘buddy’ a brother to do brotherly things with like I had my sister to do sister things with (mainly fighting over clothes 😂). So growing up I always said I wanted 4 kids, two boys & two girls, so they would have each other to do life with. Never did I think that would ever happen, especially with my fertility issues. When we were blessed with Luck & what we thought was our third & final addition I was so thrilled to get to experience three kiddos & loved every second of three kids, Zack & I had settled into life & were ‘done’ having kids, we had started moving forward with our life & past the baby stage & I had happily accepted that Luck was going to be the little sister with big brothers to do life with….then here comes God with a totally different plan, one I had held in my heart from long ago, & surprised us with our sweet Vallie Joi. I’m so excited to watch these sisters get to do life together & see what clothes they fight over 😝. I just can’t wait to watch all my kiddos together, siblings are literally the coolest thing ever.

Townes asks me every morning, “Mom why are your eyes all red & puffy?” My response most days while laughing…”Cause I’m tired dude, I haven’t slept in 6 years!” 
This where you’ll find me most of the time these days, with clean laundry on the couch that needs to be folded & two little girls fighting to sit on me.
Wednesday nights & good horses.

1 month ↯ with our littlest love 

Vallie Joi 
9lbs 5oz. We’ve gained 2lbs this month. And all of our hearts have grown about two sizes, Vallie has all of us wrapped around her little finger & we wouldn’t have it any other way. Little sis loves to nurse all day long & party all night long 🥲, she has the cutest baby cry I have ever heard. She still has her little angel kiss at the tip of her nose, every dr & nurse she’s met has said something along the lines of, “I’ve been in this industry for so many years & have never seen an angel kiss on the tip of the nose, they’re always on the forehead, eyelid, or back of the neck.” It’s as unique & beautiful as she is. Her hair has lightened up some but still so dark & such a beautiful color. We love you sis & we’re so glad God surprised us with you. We can’t wait to see all the growing you do in month 2.

Blue bonnets are something, but if I had my pick it’s Indian paint brushes all day long. I can’t get over how beautiful they are & all the different color variations.
Here’s to 36! Looking forward to more adventures with my family & good health. Thanks to everyone who took time out of there day to wish me a happy birthday. I’m a blessed old fart

Did an absolutely terrible job at taking pictures this weekend, but the few I got I just love. @westernheritageclassic weekend will always be one of my favorites of the whole year. I literally feel like a kid on Christmas leading up to it. Highlights of the weekend were getting to see so many friends & family, the shopping, the music, the food, having Kase walk up to Jake Hooker & the two of them casually having a conversation about Willie Nelson, then having Jake autograph his Willie picture, and then for Kase to turn around & get a cow tag keychain with the same Willie portrait on it & Kase sign his autograph on it & give it to Jake, who laughed & hung it on his mic stand 😂. Townes talking an older gentleman down to $10 for a big ol belt buckle, and so many more memories that will go down in the books. Literally can’t wait for next year.

Back in my braid era. 🙌🏼. I also may or may not be teaching myself to silversmith & it’s bringing me so much joy I can’t even begin to put it into words. Feeling like myself again 💛. Here’s a few pieces I’ve made so far, I’m hoping to be able to have pieces made for sale by July 🥰.

These boys of mine had their last day of kindergarten today 🥹. I don’t care what anyone says, time literally & I mean literally, moves faster once you have kids. There has to be some type of time portal parents are in & I hate it. I ask them everyday to stop growing, and they tell me Gods in charge of that part, well the other night Kase told me he didn’t want me to grow anymore because he doesn’t want me to die, 🫠😂. His solution to me not growing was for me to drink more beer. The conversation went as such…

Kase- “Goodnight mom, I love you, happy mother day…..mom when you die one day, I’ll always remember you!”
Me- “oh thanks buddy, I love you too, hopefully I’m not going anywhere anytime soon.”
Kase- “Mom you should drink more BEER so you stop growing! That way you can live forever.”
Me- “Does beer make you stop growing?”
Kase- “Yeah, your belly might get bigger, but you won’t get older.” 

Solid 6 year old logic 😂. I truly hate that time goes so fast, but I also can’t wait to see all the things these two do. I just want their young, careless, innocent souls to stick around as long as possible.
Family. 🫶🏼
Teamwork makes the dream work. #wiregatesareab

dad - according to dictionary.com 

1. a person’s father or one’s father 
2. a term of endearment used to refer to a man or boy who is admired 

3. corny or embarrassing in the way that  a father figure might be: a dad joke; the most dad story ever. 
4. handsome or stylish; amazing; to be admired 

5. to act as a father toward; act paternally toward 
6. to refer to (an admired man or boy) as “dad”:

I truly think the most important decision you make in life, is who you choose to have children with. When I say I chose one that fills all the roles as described above (especially the handsome & corny versions) I did. He’s the most amazing partner & wonderful father to our children, I’m glad I chose him to do life with & raise all these feral kids with. Happy Father’s Day @zackmcginn we love you.
8 years down & a lifetime to go. I love you so much @zackmcginn. Thanks for choosing to be mine.

I don’t know how to put into words how truly incredible this wild little spitfire is. I’m so incredibly blessed to be her mom.

-girl LOVES ice, so much so we had to buy her, her own ice machine.

-talks in full sentences. ‘No’ with some attitude is her favorite word.

-has a raspy voice 
-loves chocolate & all things sweet
-loves shoes, but doesn’t love wearing shoes 
-wants to be outside most of the time

She’s just so incredible & I love her beyond any words. Thank you God for this sweet little girl you blessed me with 2 years ago today. 

I love you Lucky. “So much”

Zacks song Empire came out two months ago and it’s something I don’t think he has gotten near enough credit for. It’s truly an incredible song if you listen to it. Truly listen to it. Ranching is the most beautiful thing in the world, but most of the time ranching isn’t what these shows share, it’s splitting ice in -20° weather, going over fence in 50+ mph winds, fixing busted water lines at midnight, digging endless post holes, patching up water troughs, & playing doctor to all the different  animals that come along with ranching. Painting pipe & repairing barns that are older then those working on it, dealing with your local NRCS, BLM, & Forest Service offices are just a few examples of things cowboys deal with on the daily, caring for cattle is the fun part & the stuff that gets shown most, but truth is ranching is so much more. It’s a legacy all in its own & like my husband says in his song, “this country will live forever, people ain’t for a little while.” Support your local rancher & farmer. They are truly the backbone of this country. And while your at it, go listen to Empire by @zackmcginn & share your videos of what ranching is
